\description{
Performs an omnibus test combining Burden, SKAT, and Fisher tests using the
Cauchy Combination Test (CCT). The omnibus test adapts to different genetic
architectures by combining multiple test statistics, providing robust power
across various scenarios.

GLOW_Omni computes:
\enumerate{
\item Burden test (optimal + equal weights)
\item SKAT test (optimal + equal weights)
\item Fisher test (optimal + equal weights)
\item CCT of SNV-level p-values (variant-level minimum p-value combination)
\item CCT combining all the above tests (final omnibus p-value)
}

The final omnibus p-value provides protection against model misspecification
and is powerful across diverse genetic architectures.
}
\details{
\strong{Algorithm}:

Internally delegates to \code{run_bsf_tests()}, which:
\enumerate{
\item For each test family in \code{test_specs}, computes optimal and equal
weights, then evaluates the weighted test statistic.
\item Combines all individual test p-values via CCT (BSF omnibus).
\item Computes SNV-level CCT from marginal p-values (if
\code{include_snv_cct = TRUE}).
\item Combines individual + SNV CCT for final omnibus p-value.
}

\strong{Transformation Details}:
\itemize{
\item Scaled effect sizes: \eqn{B^* = \sqrt{diag(M_s)} \times B / s_0}
\item Burden uses g(x) = x, df = Inf
\item SKAT uses g(x) = x^2, df = 1
\item Fisher uses g(x) = g_GFisher_two(x, df=2), df = 2
}

\strong{Output Structure} (default 3-family spec, 16 rows):
\itemize{
\item Rows 1-5: SKAT tests (BE_N, APR_N, BE_sparse, APR_sparse, equ)
\item Rows 6-8: Burden tests (BE, APR, equ)
\item Rows 9-13: Fisher tests (BE_N, APR_N, BE_sparse, APR_sparse, equ)
\item Row 14: BSF Omni (CCT of rows 1-13)
\item Row 15: SNV-level CCT
\item Row 16: Final omnibus CCT
}

With custom \code{test_specs}, the number of rows varies.

\strong{Computational Complexity}: O(k * m^2) where k is number of weight
schemes, m is number of variants
